Malcolm Macarthur’s arrest in the home of the Attorney General Patrick Connolly creates an international political storm. Charles Haughey holds a press conference to calm things down. It leads to the creation of a phrase that will haunt him for the res of the career. Episode four of seven. [ Listen to the most recent episodes, here.  ] GUBU is researched, reported and narrated by Harry McGee and edited by Enda O’Dowd. Sound mix by JJ Vernon Title music by Orakhal Graphics by Paul Scott